IIRC green only means it sees the magnet correctly, so maybe they aren’t connected. Try connecting a motor and see if you detect it. Maybe it’s only connected to the PDH/a resistor but not the rio?
Edit: Just checked the status lights and I was wrong.

It’s possible the CANcoder LED will be dim green if the magnet proximity is good but it has never seen the CAN Bus. (As opposed to bright green if both CAN and magnet are good)

How are you powering your CANcoder?
CANcoders require 12 volts, and if you power it off of 5 volts it’s possible the LED will still light up but CAN will not work.
